## Commands

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"    # Install with dev deps
pytest tests/ -v           # Run all tests
pytest tests/test_x.py -v  # Run single test file
ruff check .               # Lint
ruff format .              # Format
```

## Architecture

- `src/{{PACKAGE}}/` — Package source
  - `utils/` — Pure utility functions (one per file, re-export via __init__.py)
  - `services/` — External integrations (one per file)
  - `models/` — Data models/schemas (one per file)
  - `lib/` — Internal shared logic
- `tests/` — Tests (mirror src/ structure)

## Code Style

- Type hints on all public functions
- f-strings over .format() or %
- Pathlib over os.path
- One function/class per file in utils/, services/, models/
- Max complexity 10, max 5 args per function (enforced by ruff)
- Barrel re-exports via __init__.py in each directory

## Testing

- Framework: pytest
- Run single test: `pytest tests/test_x.py::test_name -v`
- Mirror src/ structure in tests/
- Use fixtures from `tests/conftest.py`
- No mocks unless testing external services

## Security

This repo is public. Never write actual values from `~/.env` into any file. Use env var names, `os.environ.get()`, or `<placeholder>` syntax. Use generic names (alice, bob) not real names. Use `localhost` or `<host>` not real IPs. Hookify rules and gitleaks pre-commit enforce this.

